During a summit between President Yoon of South Korea and President Biden of the United States, they reaffirmed their commitment to the strong alliance between their countries. They highlighted the historical significance of their alliance, which was forged during the Korean War when American soldiers fought to defend South Korea's freedom. The leaders also emphasized the economic benefits of their alliance, such as the KORUS FTA, which has created jobs and promoted investment in both countries. They expressed their shared values of democracy, human rights, and the rule of law, and discussed expanding their alliance to include technology and global strategic cooperation. President Yoon quoted a line from a poem by William Butler Yeats, emphasizing the importance of their friendship. President Biden praised the productive meetings and personal connection between them and raised a glass to the continued flourishing of their alliance.